stimulus:
Please carefully read the following campaign, and indicate below how much you would donate.

Once you are satisfied, press "Continue" at the bottom.

responses: {"Q0":"Jennifer is a great hard-working person who just got over a thyroid surgery and now got hit with Lymphoma. This poor woman is toughing it out after receiving hit after hit from life. I feel so bad for her and want to help out since this horrible just by itself, but following thyroid issues? I hope she gets better with help, no one deserves to go through all of this at once."}
{"Q0":"Female","Q1":"High school degree or equivalent (e.g. GED)","Q2":"$25,000 through $49,999","Q3":"Yes"}
{"Q0":"To see if people would be willing to donate more to someone they feel a connection to due to past experiences or just out of the goodness of their own hearts."}

{"Q0":"I was treated for melanoma, which is not the same as Lymphoma in any case, but I did feel some kind of connection. I was lucky that mine was caught so early that it did not have a chance to metastasize, but the anxiety I felt while waiting for the results was horrible enough as it was. The surgery was awful too, but not anywhere near as bad as a Lymphoma sufferer would go through."}
